gate: OPEN
sprint: S04
track: A
task: A1
title: "chore(deps): fix bun audit vulnerabilities — Clerk authz bypass HIGH (#1416)"
repos: [crop-front]
priority: P1
refs:
  - CROP-front#1416
requires: [TYPESCRIPT]

description: |
  bun audit reports a HIGH severity Clerk authorization bypass vulnerability.
  While unpatched, any user could potentially bypass authorization checks.
  Fix: upgrade affected Clerk package(s) to patched version. Then flip the
  audit gate from non-blocking to blocking so future HIGH/CRITICAL vulnerabilities
  stop CI.

scope:
  in:
    - Run `bun audit` — identify exact package(s) and CVE
    - Upgrade affected package(s) to patched version per advisory
    - Verify `bun audit` returns 0 HIGH/CRITICAL after upgrade
    - Flip audit gate to blocking in CI (package.json script or CI workflow)
    - Smoke: auth flows still work on localhost (sign-in, sign-out, protected routes)
  out:
    - Upgrading unrelated packages
    - Changing auth logic or Clerk configuration

acceptance:
  - `bun audit` returns 0 HIGH or CRITICAL findings
  - CI audit gate is blocking (non-zero exit on HIGH/CRITICAL)
  - Auth smoke passes on localhost

dep: none
output: bun.lock (updated) + CI workflow or package.json (audit gate flipped)
